sense.name: make violent, noisy movements
sense.examples: They swashed down upon her bed. He swashed and buckled his way into the history books.

sense.name: dash liquid on or against
sense.examples: He swashed his coffee on Josef Hirsal's shirt The nightmared ocean murmurs and swashes. He couldn't help noticing the beer swashing in the cup. But I took drinks and I've swashed it around in my mouth.

sense.name: bluster, show off, or swagger
sense.examples: He swashed about in a self- confident manner. He swashed about voting against Obama 's budget. He swashed about self-confidently.
